      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Critics argue that fear-mongering about existential AI risks has become a \"kitchen sink fallacy,\" casting a net that is far too broad and inconsistent with historical experience. They contend that strict regulation could stifle the very innovation needed to solve existential problems, creating a reactive cycle where tools are banned before they are perfected. Furthermore, they emphasize the high uncertainty of current models, suggesting that the potential for existential catastrophe is vastly overstated compared to the tangible benefits already being delivered.",
