      "content": "I see. So it's basically a choice between being overly cautious and stopping progress, or just ignoring potential catastrophe. In your professional opinion as an advisor, does the argument for existential risk carry more weight, or is it mostly just speculation compared to the actual economic benefits we're seeing right now?",
